title: Trump administration ‘failed to consider the harms’ in not supporting Snap, judge says in ruling that demands funds by Friday – live

title: US airlines cancel flights after aviation agency directive to cut air traffic
summary: United, Southwest, and Delta airlines are cutting flight schedules due to the ongoing government shutdown. The reductions reflect challenges in operations and decreased demand. This decision comes as federal workers and agencies face disruptions.

summary: Tesla's board has approved a significant compensation package for Elon Musk, contingent on key performance milestones.
